The paper deals with optimization problems and algorithm design, which are typically studied in computer science sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of randomized algorithms also suggests a connection to cs.NA. The mention of linear programming and P-matrix generalized linear complementarity problem suggests a connection to cs.CG. Finally, the mention of LP-type problems and their characterizations suggests a connection to cs.LG.
